<h3>Server</h3>

<p>Once the code is complete, a server is required to actually run the code so that a user can view it. Since we don't have easy access to a web server, we took advantage of the free student credit that Google Cloud provides and hosted the website using Google Cloud.</p>

<p>This was accomplished by running a virtual machine on the Google Cloud. This virtual machine holds all of the complied code that we wrote and when a user requests one of the pages, it runs the code and sends the web page to the user.</p>

