<h3>Domain Name</h3>

<p>After the code is running on a server, people need to be able to access the site. They could type in the external IP address of the server into their web browser to view it, but the average user will not do that. In order for someone to easily access the site, a domain name must be bought. This domain name will be the URL that people will use to access the site (like facebook.com or google.com).</p>

<p>Purchasing a domain name has been made rather simple. Go to a site like <a href="https://www.namecheap.com/">namecheap.com</a> and type in the domain name that you want. As long as the domain name isn't already in use (like facebook.com), then you can purchase it. For this project, we purchased "honors392coldwartech.xyz" as our domain name (we bought .xyz instead of .com as it was much cheaper).</p>

<p>After the domain name was purchased, we had to bind the server that is running our website to the domain name. This is done using DNS (Domain Name System) settings. This makes it so when you type in www.honors392coldwartech.xyz, the browser is actually being redirected to the IP address of the server and the website is presented to you. The current DNS settings for this website are shown below.</p>

